Acute abdomen due to acute pancreatitis--a rare presentation of leptospirosis. Even though, Leptospiral infection is not uncommon, it can have different rare presentations. Acute pancreatitis is one such rare gastrointestinal manifestation of acute pancreatitis. Apart from the typical clinical features elevated serum lipase or elastase-1, along with radiological evidence and positive leptospiral serology confirms this rare association.